

configuration user information:
$ git config --global user.name "XXX"
$ git config --global user.email "XX@XX.com"
check:
$ git config --global user.name
$ git config --global user.email

to create nicknames for commonly used commands:
create a file under drive C:/user/username
$ touch ~/.bashrc    //touch .bashrc is to create it on desktop
open .bashrc file in local machine, add:
alias git-log='git log --pretty=oneline --all --graph --abbrev-commit'
alias ll='ls -al'

create a repo locally:
create a folder in local machine
get into the folder and right click then select 'gitBash':
$ git init
$ ll
it shows up .git/ which means it's been created successfully
